<DocsLayout
  title="AI providers"
  description="Connect cloud or local AI models to Alterm, and understand the terminal-aware context model."
>
  <p>
    Alterm's AI chat block speaks to providers through a single provider abstraction, so any
    OpenAI-compatible endpoint works. Cloud keys live in your local config — never on a server.
  </p>

  <h2>Supported providers</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>OpenAI</strong> — <code>gpt-4o</code> and others</li>
    <li><strong>Anthropic</strong> — Claude models</li>
    <li><strong>Google Gemini</strong></li>
    <li><strong>xAI Grok</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Ollama</strong> — local, no API key required (the default)</li>
    <li><strong>LM Studio</strong> and any other OpenAI-compatible local server</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Configuring a provider</h2>
  <p>
    Each provider is a block under <code>[ai.providers]</code>. <code>base_url</code> can be omitted
    to use the provider's canonical endpoint; <code>api_key</code> is not needed for local
    providers.
  </p>
  <pre><code># Local Ollama (default — no key required)
[ai.providers.ollama]
model    = "llama3.2"
base_url = "http://localhost:11434/v1"

# OpenAI
[ai.providers.openai]
api_key = "sk-..."
model   = "gpt-4o"

# Anthropic
[ai.providers.anthropic]
api_key = "sk-ant-..."
model   = "claude-opus-4-5"</code></pre>

  <p>
    Set the active default in the <code>[ai]</code> block with
    <code>default_provider = "&lt;name&gt;"</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>The context model</h2>
  <p>
    Today the chat reads the <strong>focused terminal pane</strong> — it sees that pane's recent
    output, so its answers reflect what's actually on your screen. Switch focus, and the context
    follows you.
  </p>
  <p>Two richer context modes are planned:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Pinned panes</strong> <em>(planned)</em> — pin specific panes so they stay in the
      AI's view regardless of focus, for watching build output and server logs while you work
      elsewhere.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>@ mentions</strong> <em>(planned)</em> — type <code>@pane:2</code> or
      <code>@tab:ssh-prod</code> to reference a pane's output in one message without pinning it.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>AI actions <em>(planned)</em></h2>
  <p>A future update will let the AI propose actions, each behind a confirmation prompt — it proposes, you approve:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Open a new terminal pane and run a command</li>
    <li>Split the current view</li>
    <li>Open a browser pane to show documentation</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="note">
    <p>
      <strong>Available now:</strong> the AI chat panel, multi-provider streaming, and active-pane
      context ship in the current build (v0.4.0). <strong>Pinned panes</strong>,
      <strong>@&nbsp;mentions</strong>, and <strong>AI actions</strong> are on the roadmap.
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
